comment: Wish I had a choice of professors. She runied a lot of 4.0s this semester. You do all the work, hand it in early for her to 'fix' it, you make changes and it's still not good enough. All three projects were due on the same day so you never figure out how you're doing. -Just lectures at you during the whole class period. Hope you're ready for that.

She is a great teacher.  She is very funny and pationate about what she does.  She loves teaching.  We do a dance at the end of every class, it is a lot of fun and she means well.  Definately take...it's an experience

DR. Cohen makes attempts at being a genuine person, however, she fails miserably.  She definately plays favorites and makes back-handed remarks which are crass and rude.  Her lessons were non-iinformative and the work that she assigned was very much busy-work with no inspiration behind them.
Do not call upon Professor Cohen if you need help, becuase she will not be there for you!  She enjoys put downs and talks about her sons way too much.

Quite unclear and garbled.  She can be rather condescending, puts down students, picks on others, tells people that they need help, yet does not bother to assist those in need.  She was never available when needed for advisement.  Dr. Cohen did not relate the assessments to the information taught.
She is amazing in this class. She was so informative and very down to earth.  I learned a lot from her.
nice person, only thing i learned was that Gail, her childhood friend's name, is an example of a dipthong .
This women told me that I need to seek medical help and should rearrange my life to fit her into her schedule.  She told me that I had a learning disorder...WITHOUT even knowing me
the woman called me a freak - enough said
Dr. Cohen gives a lot of work but if you put the effort into it, you will do fine.  If you need help with anything, you can go to her.
She is a very nice person. The class wasn't that good, her train of thought is all over the place. The midterm and final had nothing to do with what we 'learned'
No Comments
A really nice guy BUT class had no direction and was often a waste of time.  He can very easily put you to sleep... very boring
I had him his first year and he was awful!!  Try your best to NOT have to take this man!

A litte dry, but a really nice man. He is very fair and understanding, and goes out of his way to help his students suceed. Also a very easy grader b/c he hands things back w/ corrections so you can fix them before he actually grades them. Will do anything to help.
He was rather bland and lectured without moving his hands, lips or showing any signs of life.  However, Professor Benin gave me an A for his class because I complained constantly.
Leigh Benin is by far the best part of Adelphi University.  How can you not want to emulate this man's every move.  If I can be 1/10th the Social Studies teacher he is, then I have done a good job.
Prof. Benin is awesome, he goes above and beyond to help his students succeed.
He doesn't move his lips when he talks.
Dr. Benin does not deserve the bad reputation that people have given him! He does everything he can to help his students succeed
He isn't as bad as people make him out to be.  I think he is trying hard and is a good professor
No Comments

i found him to be someone who is spiteful and vindictive. he lowered my grade because, while i handed in all the required work- and he freely admitted that to me-, some people did extra work. So, rather than raising their grades, mine was lowered.
No Comments
